---
import ApplicationLayout from '../layouts/ApplicationLayout.astro';

const articleJsonLd = {
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Disc Centrifuge | Biotech Cell Harvesting",
  "description": "Alfa Laval BTPX-205 self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge for biotech cell harvesting, pharmaceutical separation, and chemical processing.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Sanjay Prabhu MSME",
    "jobTitle": "Centrifuge Applications Engineer",
    "worksFor": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge" }
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge",
    "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com"
  }
};

const jsonLd = [
  articleJsonLd,
  {
    "@type": "Product",
    "name": "Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Biotech Centrifuge",
    "description": "Alfa Laval BTPX-205 self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge for biotech cell harvesting, pharmaceutical separation, and chemical processing. 5 GPM, 12,800 Gs.",
    "brand": { "@type": "Brand", "name": "Alfa Laval" },
    "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/",
  },
];

const toc = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'specifications', label: 'Specifications' },
  { id: 'applications', label: 'Applications' },
  { id: 'operation', label: 'Operation' },
];

const relatedProducts = [
  { label: 'Disc Stack Centrifuge Overview', href: '/disc-stack-centrifuge/', description: 'Complete disc stack centrifuge systems' },
  { label: 'Stainless Steel Centrifuges', href: '/stainless-steel-centrifuge/', description: 'Hygienic stainless steel models' },
];

const relatedApplications = [
  { label: 'Food Grade Centrifuge Systems', href: '/food-grade-centrifuge/' },
  { label: 'All Centrifuge Applications', href: '/disc-stack-centrifuge-applications/' },
  { label: 'Pilot Sample Testing', href: '/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/' },
];
---

<ApplicationLayout
  title="Alfa Laval BTPX 205 Disc Centrifuge | Biotech Cell Harvesting"
  disableTitleSuffix={true}
  description=""
  heroImage="/images/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-BTPX-205-SGD-34-CDP.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Alfa Laval BTPX 205 SGD-34-CDP"
  category="products"
  categoryLabel="Products"
  canonicalUrl="https://dolphincentrifuge.com/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  toc={toc}
  relatedProducts={relatedProducts}
  relatedApplications={relatedApplications}
>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

  <figure class="not-prose mb-6">
    <img
      src="/images/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-BTPX-205-SGD34-CDP-1-600.webp"
      alt="Alfa Laval BTPX-205-SGD34-CDP"
      loading="lazy"
      width="600"
      height="640"
      class="img-cap-600"
    />
    <figcaption><strong>Alfa Laval BTPX-205-SGD34-CDP</strong></figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>The Alfa Laval BTPX-205 is a self-cleaning centrifuge of the disc-stack type. Its design allows it to separate the liquid from liquid and solids (purifier) or liquid from solids (clarifier).</p>

  <p>The BTPX-205 features a 'partial solids' ejection feature that allows the centrifuge to purge only the solids. This feature reduces fluid losses associated with sludge ejection.</p>

  <p>The sludge ejection cycle can be timer-triggered or based on the volume processed.</p>

  <p>The centrifuge separates suspended solids such as organic cells in a broth or fine chemicals as a clarifier. When set up as a purifier, it separates solids and intermixed and immiscible liquid phases.</p>

  <p>The solids content in the process fluid can be up to 10% by volume.</p>

  <figure class="not-prose mb-6">
    <img
      src="/images/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-BTPX-205-SGD-34-CDP-600.webp"
      alt="Alfa Laval BTPX 205 SGD-34-CDP"
      loading="lazy"
      width="600"
      height="781"
      class="img-cap-600"
    />
    <figcaption><strong>Alfa Laval BTPX 205 SGD-34-CDP</strong></figcaption>
  </figure>

  <!-- Specifications -->
  <h2 id="specifications">Specifications</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8 not-prose">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
      <tbody>
        <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Model Type</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">Alfa Laval BTPX-205</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Rated Capacity</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">5 GPM on Pharma Cell Broth</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Sludge Space</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">0.25 Gallons</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Bowl RPM</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">9,650</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">G-Force</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">12,800 Gs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Motor HP:</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">7.5 HP</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Voltages:</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-text-light">230 / 460 V</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Applications -->
  <h2 id="applications">Applications</h2>

  <p>The BTPX-205 is applicable for removing suspended solids with a particle size of 0.5 t0 500 µm. The liquid centrate has a lower density than the solids.</p>

  <p>The solids content is usually in the range of 0,1 to 10% by volume. The total solids content can be from 0.1% to 10% by volume.</p>

  <p>The following are some of the popular applications of the Alfa Laval BTPX-205:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Biotechnology</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Organic Cell Harvesting</li>
        <li>Cell Growth</li>
        <li>Clarification Fermentation Broth</li>
        <li>Clarification of Cell Debris</li>
        <li>Recovery of Inclusion Body</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Pharmaceutical</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Plasma Fraction Recovery</li>
        <li>Precipitate Recovery</li>
        <li>Vaccines and Serums Production</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Chemical</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Catalyst Separation</li>
        <li>Sub-micron Particle Separation</li>
        <li>Pigments, Dyes and Toners</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p><br>The maximum process capacity of the machine is 5 Gallon/Minute.</p>

  <!-- Operation -->
  <h2 id="operation">Operation</h2>

  <p>The bio-culture fluid enters the rotating bowl of the BTPX 205 centrifuge. The bowl exerts a high g-force (12,800 Gs) on the process fluid.<br><br>The centrifugal force causes rapid sedimentation of the cells. These separated cells are auto-ejected from the centrifuge.</p>

  <p>The liquid phase (broth) moves towards the centers and exits the bowl through a separate outlet.</p>

  <p>A detailed explanation of the operation of the BTPX-205 centrifuge follows.</p>

  <figure class="not-prose mb-6">
    <img
      src="/images/alfa-laval-btpx-205-biotech-centrifuge/BTPX-205-Bowl-Cross-Section-400.webp"
      alt="BTPX 205 Bowl Cross Section"
      loading="lazy"
      width="400"
      height="400"
      class="img-cap-400"
    />
    <figcaption><strong>BTPX 205 Bowl Cross Section</strong></figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>The process fluid enters the rotating bowl of the centrifuge through a stationary inlet pipe (1). The distributor (2) accelerates the fluid before it enters the disc stack (3).</p>

  <p>The separation of the solids from the liquid happens in the inter-disc space.</p>

  <p>The clear liquid moves towards the center of the bowl. A paring disc (4) pumps out the clear centrate.</p>

  <p>The denser solids move towards the bowl periphery. From there, their ejection happens through the centrifuge cyclone.</p>

  <p>A hydraulic mechanism located under the bowl separation space causes the sludge ejection. This mechanism forces the sliding piston (5) downward, opening the solids ejection ports (6) at the bowl periphery.</p>

  <p>The cyclone reduces the high ejection velocity of the solids.</p>

  <p>Dolphin Centrifuge has an Alfa Laval BTPX-205 Biotechnology centrifuge systems in stock for sale.</p>


</ApplicationLayout>
